Atomic Electron Pair Contributions:
----------------------------------
  D2(A,A) = Average Number of Electron Pairs Formed in Atom A
          = (1/2)[N(A) * N(A) - LI(A)]
  D2(A,A') = Half of Average Number of Electron Pairs Formed
             Between Atom A and Other Atoms of Molecule
          = (1/2)[N(A) * N(A') - DI(A,A') / 2]
  D2(A,Mol) = D2(A,A) + D2(A,A')
Note:  ECP-Modeled Core Electrons are NOT Included Here
See "2EDM Note".
